ry Compilation Office, *Toba City History: Upper and Lower Volumes*, 1991. * Hosoi Keiji, "Seihō Shimada and the Haiku Literary Movement," *Haiku Literature Quarterly*, 1996. * Mie Prefecture Board of Education, *Historical Pathways of Ise: Asama-Toba Road and Others*, 1986. == Related Articles == * {{ill|Ise-Shima National Park|ja|伊勢志摩国立公園|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Navigation|ja|航路|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Landmarks|ja|航路標識|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Hiking|ja|ハイキング|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Hiyoriyama (Toba City)|ja|日和山 (鳥羽市)|12=draft|12=draft}} == External Links == * [http://maikoh.net/corp/event/aominezan/ Shofuku-ji Temple - Aonomine Mountain Official Page]
